n = int(input())

d = {}

for i in range(n):
    country, year = input().split()
    year = int(year)
    if country not in d:
        d[country] = []
    d[country].append(year)

q = int(input())

for i in range(q):
    country, k = input().split()
    k = int(k)
    print(d[country][k-1])

from collections import defaultdict

n = int(input())
trips = defaultdict(list)

for _ in range(n):
    c, y = input().split()
    trips[c].append(int(y))

q = int(input())

for _ in range(q):
    c, k = input().split()
    print(trips[c][int(k) - 1])

n = int(input())
d = dict()
for _ in range(n):
    country, year = input().split()
    year = int(year)
    if country in d:
        d[country].append(year)
    else:
        d[country] = [year]

q = int(input())
for _ in range(q):
    country, k = input().split()
    k = int(k)
    print(sorted(d[country])[k-1])

n = int(input())
trips = []
for i in range(n):
    country, year = input().split()
    year = int(year)
    trips.append((country, year))

q = int(input())
queries = []
for i in range(q):
    country, k = input().split()
    k = int(k)
    queries.append((country, k))

for query in queries:
    country, k = query
    trips_to_country = [trip for trip in trips if trip[0] == country]
    trips_to_country.sort(key=lambda t: t[1], reverse=True)
    print(trips_to_country[k - 1][1])
